  "text": "Both the laboratory measurements and the Hydra sensor monitoring data in frozen soil resulted in sets of depthwise soil water retention (h p vs. θ w ) data for the four farmers' fi elds and the rangeland soil. Th e Hydra sensor retention data were limited to the fi rst freezing cycle during each winter so that only data points for which the temperature was lower than any previous temperature during that winter were included. Th is procedure was recommended by [CITATION_1] to limit the effect of hysteresis on the water retention data. Th e van Genuchten (1980) soil water retention model was fi tted to the individual h p -θ w data sets, establishing separate curves for the laboratory and Hydra sensor monitoring data for each depth:",
